com.i2group.apollo.model.data.transport

Class SecurityAccessPermission

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.i2group.apollo.model.data.transport.SecurityAccessPermission

  • public final class SecurityAccessPermission
extends Object
    A specification of the SecurityAccessLevel associated with a particular SecurityDimension value.

    Objects in the Analysis Repository that use security permissions have either a collection containing at least one SecurityAccessPermission per "access" SecurityDimension, or a collection identifying SecurityTags that fulfill the same requirement.

    Throughout its lifetime, a SecurityAccessPermission is subject to validation rules:

    • The identifier returned by getDimensionId() must reference a SecurityDimension from the SecuritySchema's "access" dimensions.
    • The value returned by getValue() must match a value from SecurityDimension.getValues() for that dimension.
    Since:
    1.0

    • Constructor Detail

      • SecurityAccessPermission

        public SecurityAccessPermission(String dimensionId,
                        String dimensionValue,
                        SecurityAccessLevel accessLevel)
        Constructs a new SecurityAccessPermission.
        Parameters:
        dimensionId - A String containing the identifier of the SecurityDimension that this SecurityAccessPermission refers to. This must match the identifier of an "access" SecurityDimension in the active SecuritySchema.
        dimensionValue - A String containing the value of the SecurityDimension that this permission applies to. This must be one of the valid values of the SecurityDimension identified in dimensionId.
        accessLevel - The SecurityAccessLevel to be associated with the named SecurityDimension in this SecurityAccessPermission.
